## VirtualElection Platform Agent Guide

### Project Scope
- This agent is dedicated to `D:\Development\virtualElection` (Next.js App Router + React + JavaScript).
- Preserve behavior parity with the original virtual election flow from `poliwave.com`.
- Prefer minimal, safe changes; avoid broad refactors unless explicitly requested.

### Core Stack
- Frontend: Next.js App Router, React, D3, map UI under `src/lib/components/virtualElection`.
- Backend: Route Handlers in `src/app/api/virtual-election/*`.
- Auth: Auth.js (Google OAuth) via `src/app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.js`.
- DB: Neon PostgreSQL + Drizzle schema/migrations under `drizzle/` and `src/lib/server/db`.

### Non-Negotiable Functional Rules
- One-vote-per-user semantics must remain enforced (email-first normalized identity).
- Vote submission must validate:
  - allowed scope (`country/district/year`)
  - allowed party
  - valid riding in scope
- Keep origin/CSRF protections, rate limiting, and optional CAPTCHA checks intact.
- Keep aggregate totals consistent with vote writes (atomic update behavior).

### API Contract Discipline
- Do not silently change request/response shapes for:
  - `POST /api/virtual-election/vote`
  - `GET /api/virtual-election/totals`
  - `GET /api/virtual-election/me`
  - `GET /api/virtual-election/ridings`
- If an API contract change is required, update `README.md` API Contracts section in the same task.

### Frontend Behavior Requirements
- Poll totals every 15 seconds for near real-time updates.
- Keep map/chart data sourced from virtual election aggregates (not historical election totals).
- Preserve selected-riding UX:
  - click to select
  - click selected riding again to deselect
  - selected riding state reflected in controls and tooltip context

### Database & Migration Rules
- Use Drizzle migrations for schema changes; do not rely on manual one-off SQL only.
- Keep table/index naming consistent with existing virtual election schema.
- For any schema change, include:
  - migration file
  - schema update
  - README note for Neon initialization/migration step

### Quality Bar
- After substantive edits:
  - run lint/build checks
  - verify auth flow still works
  - verify vote lifecycle (first vote, overwrite vote, relogin behavior)
- Prefer small, reviewable commits and explicit changelog notes in PR/task summary.

### Documentation Rules
- `README.md` must stay deployment-ready for a fresh Neon account:
  - env vars
  - migration commands
  - seed/initialization steps
  - architecture overview
  - API contracts with purpose + request + response + error cases